The "Request contains an invalid argument" error is occurring because your Galaxy A54 records audio at a very high quality (48,000 Hz), but the Gemini AI strictly expects standard speech quality (16,000 Hz). Sending the high-quality audio directly causes the system to reject the request.

I will fix this by adding a "Downsampler" to the recorder. This acts like a funnel, converting your phone's high-speed audio into the exact 16,000 Hz format the AI requires, ensuring smooth transcription.

I'm also removing the conflicting code in `index.html` to prevent any other stability issues.

