I have identified the specific cause of the "Invalid Argument" error.

**The Issue:**
Your Galaxy phone records at **48,000 Hz**. While I tried to tell the AI to accept this rate, the Gemini Live API is very strict and often rejects anything that isn't exactly **16,000 Hz** or **24,000 Hz**. Sending 48k causes the "Invalid Argument" crash.

**The Fix:**
Instead of trying to convert the audio manually (which is complex and error-prone), I will force the **web browser itself** to handle the conversion. Modern mobile browsers (Chrome on Android) are very good at this. I will tell the browser "Give me 16,000 Hz audio," and it will handle the complex math to convert your 48k microphone input perfectly before my code even sees it.

I will also add a safety catch for the "Wake Lock" error so the app doesn't crash if the screen permission is denied.

