The error "Request contains an invalid argument" persists because your Android phone is ignoring the command to record at 16,000 Hz and is forcing 48,000 Hz (high quality) anyway. The AI rejects this high-speed data immediately.

**The Ultimate Fix:**
I will stop asking the phone to change its settings (since it ignores us) and instead implement a **Manual Audio Converter** inside the app.
1.  The app will accept whatever speed your phone gives (e.g., 48k).
2.  The app will mechanically calculate and reduce the data to 16k code-side.
3.  It will send this cleaned 16k audio to the AI.

This guarantees the AI gets exactly what it wants, regardless of what phone you use.

I am also removing the `importmap` from `index.html` again, as your file dump showed it was still there, and it causes version conflicts.

