I will update the app to address the "Invalid Argument" error and improve audio quality.

**The Plan:**
1.  **Architecture Update:** I will switch the audio processing to use the **Browser's Native Resampler** (AudioContext at 16,000Hz). This is cleaner and more compatible than the manual math loop I added previously. It ensures the audio sent to the AI is perfect, whether it's a Voice Note or a Lecture.
2.  **Noise Cancellation:** I will explicitly tell the phone's microphone to turn on **Noise Suppression** and **Echo Cancellation**. This filters out background chatter and air conditioning noise before it even reaches the AI.
3.  **Fixing "Invalid Argument":** This error usually happens when "Speaker Separation" (Diarization) receives noisy or weirdly formatted audio. By cleaning the audio and forcing 16kHz via the browser, this error should disappear.

